MultiChoice Nigeria says it will offer its DStv and GOtv decoders at special discounted prices during this year’s Lagos International Trade Fair. The firm’s Chief Customer Officer, Martin Mabutho, said the special trade fair discount would give more Nigerians the opportunity to enjoy quality video entertainment during the festive season. He said the fair remained a great platform to showcase products and services as well as have one-on-one interactions with customers. “On offer is a great selection of over 150 local and international channels that showcase the best football leagues live and in HD, fresh movies and series, kids’ shows, local dramas, telenovela, reality TV shows and many more. We have all these available on different packages on the DStv and GOtv that suit various lifestyles and pockets,” Mabutho said. According to him, shoppers who visit the DStv and GOtv stands during the fair will enjoy discounts up to 10 per cent on the DStv HD decoder with one month compact subscription and GOtv decoder bundled with one-month Max subscription. “They will also have available to them other value-added services such as the DStv Now, the mobile streaming app, and MyDStv and MyGOtv self-service apps,” he added. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com  